description.narrative: Maternal and Adolescent Immunization.Priority countries have technical capacity and resources to eliminate maternal and newborn tetanus and ensure its sustainability, and to provide HPV vaccination to adolescents in selected countries, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every Child to Survive and Thrive By 2021, countries apply child-sensitive policies, innovative community-centered approaches and evidence, to implement development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that enable Every Child to Survive and Thrive

description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF supported four countries in conducting MNTE campaigns, reaching 8 million women of reproductive age. The EQUIST MNTE module was introduced to the field for online risk analysis and categorization of districts. Alternative methods and tools were identified for validation in countries facing access issues and MNTE sustainability. The post-2020 MNTE strategic plan was developed, and MNTE sustainability guidelines disseminated. UNICEF supported three additional countries to rollout HPV vaccine in 9–14-year-old girls. The total number of countries introducing HPV vaccine with UNICEF’s support reached 18. 2.8 million girls in target countries received their final dose of HPV vaccine. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/03/2022
